IP Addressing in a VPC

IP addresses enable communication:

Between resources inside the VPC

Between VPC resources and the internet

EC2 uses IPv4 by default

A VPC must be created with an IPv4 CIDR block (e.g., /16)

2. Private IP Address

Assigned to every EC2 instance

Used for internal communication inside the VPC

âŒ Not reachable from the internet

Does not change during instance lifetime

ğŸ“Œ EXAM TIP:
Private IPs are used for east-west traffic (instance-to-instance).

3. Public IPv4 Address

Required for internet access

Assigned from AWS public IP pool

âœ” Reachable over the internet

âŒ Not static

Changes when instance is stopped & started

Released when instance is terminated

Key Exam Facts

Not associated with your AWS account

Cannot manually attach/detach

Controlled by:

Subnet â€œAuto-assign public IPâ€

Instance launch settings

4. Elastic IP Address (EIP)
What is an Elastic IP?

Static, persistent public IPv4 address

Allocated to your AWS account

Can be:

Associated

Disassociated

Re-associated to another instance

Why Use Elastic IPs?

High availability & failover

IP does not change

Useful with Route 53

ğŸ“Œ Failover Scenario (EXAM FAVORITE):

EIP moves from failed EC2 â†’ healthy EC2

End users see no outage

Important Elastic IP Rules

When EIP is associated:

Instanceâ€™s public IPv4 is released

âŒ Cannot convert public IP â†’ Elastic IP

âŒ Charged hourly if NOT attached to a running instance

Works only with IPv4

5. IPv4 vs IPv6 (VERY IMPORTANT FOR EXAM)
Feature	IPv4	IPv6
VPC CIDR size	/16 to /28	Fixed /56
Subnet CIDR	/16 to /28	Fixed /64
Public vs Private	âœ” Yes	âŒ No
NAT required	âœ” Yes	âŒ No
Elastic IP support	âœ” Yes	âŒ No
Internet reachable	Public IPv4 only	All IPv6

ğŸ“Œ EXAM GOLD POINT:
ğŸ‘‰ All IPv6 addresses are public

6. Internet Connectivity Requirements

To access the internet:

Internet Gateway (IGW) attached to VPC

Route table entry:

0.0.0.0/0 â†’ IGW (IPv4)

::/0 â†’ IGW (IPv6)

Security Group allows traffic

7. Controlling Internet Access

Security Groups

Network ACLs

Route Tables

For IPv6:

Access controlled ONLY via routing + security rules

8. One-Line Summary (EXAM READY)

Private IP = internal, Public IP = temporary internet access, Elastic IP = static public IPv4 for failover & persistence.

